e Gruyter]] |location=Munich |isbn=978-3-11-049520-1 |language=de| series=[[Die Verfolgung und Ermordung der europ\u00e4ischen Juden durch das nationalsozialistische Deutschland 1933-1945]] [The Persecution and Murder of European Jews by Nazi Germany 1933-1945]|volume=13 |chapter=Einf\u00fchrung: Slowakei |trans-chapter=Introduction: Slovakia||pp=18\u201345}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Kamenec |first1=Ivan|chapter=The Slovak state, 1939\u20131945 |editor1-last=Teich |editor1-first=Mikul\u00e1\u0161 |editorlink=Mikul\u00e1\u0161 Teich|editor2-last=Kov\u00e1\u010d |editor2-first=Du\u0161an |editor2-link=Du\u0161an Kov\u00e1\u010d |editor3-last=Brown |editor3-first=Martin D. |title=Slovakia in History|title-link=Slovakia in History |date=2011 |publisher=Cambridge University Press |location=Cambridge |isbn=978-1-139-49494-6|language=en|doi=10.1017/CBO9780511780141|ref={{sfnref|Kamenec|2011a}}|pp=175\u2013192}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Kub\u00e1tov\u00e1 |first1=Hana |editor1-last=Henry |editor1-first=Patrick |title=Jewish Resistance Against the Nazis|title-link=Jewish Resistance Against the Nazis (book) |date=2014 |publisher=[[Catholic University of America Press]] |location=Washington, D.C. |isbn=978-0-8132-2589-0 |pages=504\u2013518 | |language=en |chapter=Jewish Resistance in Slovakia, 1938\u20131945}}\n* {{cite book |first=Nina |last=Paulovi\u010dov\u00e1 |editor1-first = John-Paul |editor1-last = Himka |editor2-first = Joanna Beata |editor2-last =  Michlic |title=Bringing the Dark Past to Light. The Reception of the Holocaust in Postcommunist Europe.|title-link=Bringing the Dark Past to Light |chapter=The \"Unmasterable Past\"? The Reception of the Holocaust in Postcommunist Slovakia|location=Lincoln |publisher=University of Nebraska Press |year=2013 |isbn=978-0-8032-2544-2  |pp=549\u2013590}}\t\n*{{cite encyclopedia|entry=Slovakia|last1=Rothkirchen|first1=Livia |authorlink=Livia Rothkirchen|pp=595\u2013600 |editor1-last=Laqueur |editor1-first=Walter |editor-link=Walter Laqueur|editor2-last=Baumel |editor2-first=Judith Tydor |title=Holocaust Encyclopedia |date=2001 |publisher=Yale University Press |location=New Haven |language=en|isbn=978-0-300-08432-0|}}\n*{{cite book |last1=T\u00f6nsmeyer |first1=Tatjana|authorlink=Tatjana T\u00f6nsmeyer |editor1-last=Dean |editor1-first=Martin|editor1-link=Martin C. Dean |editor2-last=Goschler |editor2-first=Constantin |editor3-last=Ther |editor3-first=Philipp |title=Robbery and Restitution: The Conflict over Jewish Property in Europe |date=2007 |publisher=Berghahn Books |location=New York |isbn=9780857455642 |pages=81\u201396 ||language=en |chapter=The Robbery of Jewish Property in Eastern European States Allied with Nazi Germany}}\n{{refend}}\n\n====Book reviews====\n{{refbegin|35em|indent=yes}}\n*{{cite journal |last1=Cichopek-Gajraj |first1=Anna |title=Nepokrade\u0161! N\u00e1lady a postoje slovensk\u00e9 spole\u010dnosti k \u017eidovsk\u00e9 ot\u00e1zce, 1938\u20131945 [Thou shall not steal! Moods and attitudes of Slovak society toward the Jewish question] |journal=East European Jewish Affairs |date=2018 |volume=48 |issue=2 |pages=253\u2013255 |doi=10.1080/13501674.2018.1505360|}}\n*{{cite journal |last1=Johnson |first1=Owen V. |title=\u017didovsk\u00e1 komunita na Slovensku medzi ceskoslovenskou parlamentnou demokraciou a slovensk\u00fdm \u0161t\u00e1tom v stredoeur\u00f3pskom kontexte, Eduard Ni\u017enansk\u00fd (Pre\u0161ov, Slovakia: Universum, 1999), 292 pp., 200 crowns (Slovak). |journal=Holocaust and Genocide Studies |date=2005 |volume=19 |issue=2 |pages=314\u2013317 |doi=10.1093/hgs/dci033|}}\n{{refend}}\n\n====Theses====\n{{refbegin|35em|indent=yes}}\n*{{cite thesis|degree=PhD|editor-last=Himka|editor-first=John-Paul|editor-link=John-Paul  Himka |last1=Paulovi\u010dov\u00e1 |first1=Nina |title=Rescue of Jews in the Slovak State (1939\u20131945) |date=2012 |url=https://era.library.ualberta.ca/items/e8340da1-7b46-40cc-95e1-d57665a23e34 |language=en|doi=10.7939/R33H33|institution=[[Univer