y and memory |journal=Holocaust Studies |date=2017|volume=23 |issue=1\u20132 |pages=1\u201316 |doi=10.1080/17504902.2016.1209838|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/310824429}}\n:{{cite journal |last1=Legge |first1=Jerome S. |title=Collaboration, Intelligence, and the Holocaust: Ferdinand \u010eur\u010dansk\u00fd, Slovak Nationalism, and the Gehlen Organization |journal=Holocaust and Genocide Studies |date=2018 |volume=32 |issue=2 |pages=224\u2013248 |doi=10.1093/hgs/dcy029|issn=8756-6583}}\n:{{cite journal |last1=L\u00f4n\u010d\u00edkov\u00e1 |first1=Michala |title=Was the antisemitic propaganda a catalyst for tensions in the Slovak-Jewish relations? |journal=Holocaust Studies |date=2017 |volume=23 |issue=1\u20132 |pages=76\u201398 |doi=10.1080/17504902.2016.1209839 }}\n:{{cite journal |last1=Ni\u017e\u0148ansk\u00fd |first1=Eduard |title=The discussions of Nazi Germany on the deportation of Jews in 1942 \u2013 the examples of Slovakia, Rumania and Hungary |url=http://www.historickycasopis.sk/pdf/HCsupplement2011.pdf|journal=Historick\u00fd \u010dasopis |date=2011 |volume=59 |issue=Supplement |pages=111\u2013136|issn=0018-2575}}\n:{{cite journal |last1=Ni\u017e\u0148ansk\u00fd |first1=Eduard |title=On Relations between the Slovak Majority and Jewish Minority During World War II |journal=[[Yad Vashem Studies]] |date=2014 |volume=42 |issue=2 |pages=47-90 |issn=0084-3296}}\n:{{cite journal |first=Nina |last1=Paulovi\u010dov\u00e1 |title=Holocaust Memory and Antisemitism in Slovakia: The Postwar Era to the Present |journal=[[Antisemitism Studies]]|publisher=Indiana University Press |date=2018 |volume=2 |issue=1 |pages=4\u201334|doi=10.2979/antistud.2.1.02}}\n:{{cite journal|last1=\u0160indel\u00e1\u0159ov\u00e1 |first1=Lenka |title=Einsatzgruppe H na povstaleck\u00e9m Slovensku (1944\u20131945) a pov\u00e1le\u010dn\u00e9 trestn\u00ed st\u00edh\u00e1n\u00ed|trans-title=Einsatzgruppe H in Uprising-era Slovakia (1944\u20131945) and Postwar Prosecution |url=http:/